g&gt;&lt;div id=3Dygrp-msg&gt;&lt;div id=3Dygrp-text&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hi all,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I&#39;m starting to =
think about direction for the next SharpNEAT&lt;br&gt;iteration. There&#39;s been a l=
ot of talk recently about novelty search&lt;br&gt;versus objective search, and ma=
ybe mixtures of the two. I myself&lt;br&gt;talked about how in the natural world =
organisms are separated in both&lt;br&gt;behavioural space (i.e. novel behaviour =
is less likely to compete for&lt;br&gt;the same resources as existing behaviours)=
 but also geographical&lt;br&gt;space, and I think that geographical space is a k=
ey factor that is&lt;br&gt;missing from NEAT based search currently, and possibly=
 EC as a whole,&lt;br&gt;with the caveat there may be other research groups with =
work in that&lt;br&gt;area that I&#39;m unaware of.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;My current plan is to focu=
s on this geographical space idea for this&lt;br&gt;iteration because it is the s=
implest to implement. Dealing with&lt;br&gt;behavioural space is potentially more=
 complicated because how to&lt;br&gt;compare behaviour varies across problem doma=
ins and how you identify&lt;br&gt;the key factors to compare is probably a non-tr=
ivial problem. I want&lt;br&gt;to try and tackle this at some point, but I&#39;m also=
 keen to explore the&lt;br&gt;geo-space idea.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What does this all mean in p=
ractical terms?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SharpNEAT is a kit of parts that allows you to swap =
in replacement&lt;br&gt;parts such as an alternative genetic representation and/o=
r associated&lt;br&gt;genetic operators (recombination, mutation, etc) with minim=
al impact&lt;br&gt;on other parts in the kit (in principle anyway). I&#39;m proposing=
 to&lt;br&gt;provide an alternative evolution algorithm class that replaces NEAT&#39;=
s&lt;br&gt;genome based speciation (which clusters genomes into K clusters in&lt;br&gt;=
genetic space), with a geographical space alternative (I&#39;ll call it&lt;br&gt;geo-=
space for short).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The idea is that we have some cartesian/euclidean =
space (probably a&lt;br&gt;square 2D space initially to keep the code simple, but=
 3D or &#39;globe&#39;&lt;br&gt;space (2-sphere) are reasonable alternatives). The seed g=
enomes are&lt;br&gt;each assigned a random coord in the geo-space and this will b=
e fixed&lt;br&gt;for the life of that genome. So we are basically adding a physic=
al&lt;br&gt;attribute to the genome such that our population members are probably=
&lt;br&gt;better referred to as organisms (or agents or population members).&lt;br&gt;I=
&#39;ll use &#39;agent&#39; because it&#39;s easier to type :)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Agent fitness is now =
adjusted by population density at the agent&#39;s&lt;br&gt;geo-location, this allows =
really bad agents to survive so long as they&lt;br&gt;are in a sparse region of g=
eo-space, thus allowing for some diversity&lt;br&gt;of the genome pool.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Re=
production - I haven&#39;t put much thought into this but the two&lt;br&gt;options I =
see are to create offspring agents near to their parent(s)&lt;br&gt;versus random=
ly scattered. Probably some &#39;dispersion&#39; variable will&lt;br&gt;define the amount=
 of scattering with 0 being atop of the parent (or&lt;br&gt;between the two?) and=
 1 being totally random. (Question: Is e.g. seed&lt;br&gt;scattering in nature ga=
ussian?). Clearly if agent&#39;s are spawned near&lt;br&gt;their parent&#39;s we would ex=
pect to see clusters of agent&#39;s with similar&lt;br&gt;behaviour, and that cluster=
ing will increase population density and&lt;br&gt;therefore lower the fitness of =
agent&#39;s in that cluster. So there is a&lt;br&gt;form of fitness sharing going on,=
 but as I say, I haven&#39;t really&lt;br&gt;thought through the implications and dyn=
amics of that. But it would be&lt;br&gt;interesting to set up, play with and obse=
rve what happens.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Factoring in behavioural space considerations shou=
ld be possible at a&lt;br&gt;later date, e.g. fitness at a geo-location is not ad=
justed down if an&lt;br&gt;agent has novel behaviour compared to other agent&#39;s at=
 that&lt;br&gt;geo-location.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As per usual - any thoughts and feedback are =
welcome.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Colin&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=3DMsoNormal&gt;&lt;span s=
